{"key":"processedPost-6336617","value":{"id":6336617,"first":6336439,"last":6336800,"when":1165352100,"utime":"12/05/06 10:55 PM","cleanedPost":"Wick type humidifiers are not suitable for mycology.<br />Cool mists work very well placed on the bottom shelf of a greenhouse. This has become a common way to humidify mini-greenhouses. I run mine for only a minute or two at a time, followed by a couple of minutes off time.  This, along with trays of damp perlite on the floor, allows me to maintain 95% to 100% humidity.<br />The reason for putting them on the bottom shelf or floor is that the mist shoots four to five feet up from the discharge opening.  <br />Just leave a flap or two open for FAE.<br />RR"}}